author: wn.com
title: Republican Trump going back on the stump in Massachusetts
text: The Republican presidential front-runner is taking his campaign to Tyngsborough, northwest of Boston, where he'll attend a rally at an elementary school. Friday evening's stop follows a speech Trump delivered to about 5,000 people at a racetrack in Virginia, where he had disparaging words for U.S. Sen. Bernie Sanders of Vermont, a self-described "democratic socialist." ...
